{"questionId":"12267","questionHtml":"<p class=\"indent1\" style=\"margin-top:12pt;text-align:left;\">Find the values of <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"a\">\n  <mi>a</mi>\n</math></span> and <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"b\">\n  <mi>b</mi>\n</math></span>&nbsp;given that the matrix&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"A = \\left( {\\begin{array}{*{20}{c}}  a&amp;{ - 4}&amp;{ - 6} \\\\   { - 8}&amp;5&amp;7 \\\\   { - 5}&amp;3&amp;4  \\end{array}} \\right)\">\n  <mi>A</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mtable rowspacing=\"4pt\" columnspacing=\"1em\">\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mi>a</mi>\n          </mtd>\n          <mtd>\n            <mrow>\n              <mo>−</mo>\n              <mn>4</mn>\n            </mrow>\n          </mtd>\n          <mtd>\n            <mrow>\n              <mo>−</mo>\n              <mn>6</mn>\n            </mrow>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mrow>\n              <mo>−</mo>\n              <mn>8</mn>\n            </mrow>\n          </mtd>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>5</mn>\n          </mtd>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>7</mn>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mrow>\n              <mo>−</mo>\n              <mn>5</mn>\n            </mrow>\n          </mtd>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>3</mn>\n          </mtd>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>4</mn>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n      </mtable>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>&nbsp;is the inverse of the matrix <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"B = \\left( {\\begin{array}{*{20}{c}}  1&amp;2&amp;{ - 2} \\\\   3&amp;b&amp;1 \\\\   { - 1}&amp;1&amp;{ - 3}  \\end{array}} \\right)\">\n  <mi>B</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mtable rowspacing=\"4pt\" columnspacing=\"1em\">\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mtd>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>2</mn>\n          </mtd>\n          <mtd>\n            <mrow>\n              <mo>−</mo>\n              <mn>2</mn>\n            </mrow>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>3</mn>\n          </mtd>\n          <mtd>\n            <mi>b</mi>\n          </mtd>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mrow>\n              <mo>−</mo>\n              <mn>1</mn>\n            </mrow>\n          </mtd>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mtd>\n          <mtd>\n            <mrow>\n              <mo>−</mo>\n              <mn>3</mn>\n            </mrow>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n      </mtable>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><em>AB</em> = <em>I</em></p>\n<p>(<em>AB</em>)<sub>11</sub>&nbsp;= 1&nbsp;⇒ <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"a\">\n  <mi>a</mi>\n</math></span> – 12 + 6 = 1,&nbsp; &nbsp; giving <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"a\">\n  <mi>a</mi>\n</math></span>&nbsp;= 7&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(A1) (C1) </strong></em></p>\n<p>(<em>AB</em>)<sub>22</sub>&nbsp;= 1 ⇒ –16 + 5<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"b\">\n  <mi>b</mi>\n</math></span>&nbsp;+ 7 = 1,&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;giving <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"b\">\n  <mi>b</mi>\n</math></span>&nbsp;= 2&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(A1) (C1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"12267","referenceCode":"EXM.1.AHL.TZ0.43a","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find the values of a and b given that the matrix A = ( a − 4 − 6 − 8 5 7 − 5 3 4 ) is the inverse of the matrix B = ( 1 2 − 2 3 b 1 − 1 1 − 3 ) .","paper":"1","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 1—Number and algebra","AHL 1.14—Introduction to matrices"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}